English and Bough begin their odyssey of farcical pranks: dressed as waiters, they set fire to a flashy French restaurant; they wreak havoc as they smuggle themselves aboard Volta's luxury yacht; and English triggers sheer anarchy when he tries to use a VR headset to familiarize himself with the inside of Volta's house.
There is certainly a lot of work behind the latter sequence, but even though the film is both charming and fast-paced, it has an air of children's TV around it.
Pretty moderate all in all.
