This means solving problems in the housing market.
The UK will always be open to people who want to live, work and build a life here.
But it can’t be right when it’s as easy for people who don’t live in the UK, and even for companies based abroad, to buy homes as for hard-working residents of our country.
For too many people, the dream of owning a home has become a distant dream, and homelessness is still an unworthy fact."
